 To generate a robot favicon in Google Chrome, you need to follow these steps:

1. Create a 16x16 pixel image for your favicon. Make sure it is a .png file.
2. In your project folder, create a new file called `manifest.json`. Add the following code to the file:
```json
{
  "name": "Your Project Name",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "A short description of your extension",
  "manifest_version": 2,
  "icons": {
    "16": "path/to/your/favicon.png"
  },
  "permissions": ["activeTab"],
  "browser_action": {
    "default_icon": {
      "16": "path/to/your/favicon.png"
    }
  }
}
```
1. Replace `path/to/your/favicon.png` with the actual path to your favicon image in the `manifest.json` file.
2. Create a new folder called `dist`. In the `dist` folder, create a new file called `index.html`. Add the following code to the file:
```php
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="icon" href="manifest.json">
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Your website content goes here -->
  </body>
</html>
```
1. In the `dist` folder, create a new file called `background.js`. Add the following code to the file:
```javascript
chrome.browserAction.onClicked.addListener(function(tab) {
  chrome.tabs.update({url: "http://www.example.com"});
});
```
1. Replace `http://www.example.com` with the URL of the website you want to associate with your favicon.
2. Create a new file called `package.json`. Add the following code to the file:
```json
{
  "name": "Your Project Name",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "A short description of your extension",
  "main": "background.js",
  "manifest_version": 2,
  "browser_action": {
    "default_icon": {
      "16": "path/to/your/favicon.png"
    }
  },
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name"
  },
  "author": "",
  "license": "ISC"
}
```
1. Replace `path/to/your/favicon.png`, `http://www.example.com`, and other placeholders with the appropriate values for your project.
2. Open Google Chrome and go to `chrome://extensions`. Enable Developer Mode, click "Load unpacked", and select the root folder of your project (the one containing `manifest.json`).
3. Your extension should now be installed in Chrome. You can test it by clicking on the favicon you've created in the extensions menu.

Note: The above code is a basic example to create a robot favicon extension for Google Chrome. Depending on your project requirements, you may need to make additional changes or add more functionality.
